 About the the author...
 
 
 In case you were wondering what authority I have in creating such
 an archive, well let me put your mind to rest. I hold a diploma
 in 3D Design, an honours degree in consumer product design, I am
 a full-time product designer with a respected product design
 consultant (who I won't name because they are nothing to do with
 this, and may cause confusion.)
 
 In my spare time I program C on the Amiga, mess with 3D stuff in
 Lightwave, and produce the odd protracker module.
 
 Because of my profession I use Apple Macs and PCs at work, so I
 have the added advantage of being able to look at the faults of
 the Amiga objectively, rather than with a die-hard attitude that
 some people have, I then used this experience constructively to
 help with the development of this archive.
 
 You may think I'm sounding off here, but I think my background
 makes this archive somewhat different than the others, and
 should be stated.


